# Vitest Testing Conventions

## What to Test
- Test behavior, not implementation — test what a function does, not how
- Every composable gets a unit test
- Every API route gets an integration test (mock the DB, not the route)
- Do not test Vue internals (reactivity system, lifecycle hooks themselves)

## Test Structure
```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — clear Arrange / Act / Assert
describe('useCounter', () => {
  it('increments the count by 1', () => {
    const { count, increment } = useCounter()
    increment()
    expect(count.value).toBe(1)
  })
})

// ❌ BAD — vague name, no structure
test('works', () => { ... })
```

## Naming
- Test files: `<subject>.test.ts` colocated with source, or in `__tests__/`
- Describe blocks: the unit under test (`useCounter`, `AuthService`)
- It blocks: `'<does something> when <condition>'`

## Mocking
- Mock external dependencies (HTTP, filesystem, DB) — never in unit tests mock the module under test
- Use `vi.mock()` at the top of the file, not inside tests
- Reset mocks in `beforeEach` — never rely on test order

## Coverage
- Aim for meaningful coverage, not 100% — focus on critical paths and edge cases
- Run `vitest --coverage` before committing a new feature
